<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Linda Gottfredson, "Mainstream Science on Intelligence", <i>Intelligence</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Revised edition, p.45</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Revised edition, p.45</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFYork.2C_RichardClark.2C_Brett2006">York, Richard; Clark, Brett (February 2006). <a href="http://www.monthlyreview.org/0206yorkclark.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.monthlyreview.org/0206yorkclark.htm" rel="nofollow">"Debunking as Positive Science: Reflections in Honor of the 25th Anniversary of Stephen Jay Gould's The Mismeasure of Man"</a>. <i>Monthly Review</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.monthlyreview.org/0206yorkclark.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.monthlyreview.org/0206yorkclark.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.monthlyreview.org/0206yorkclark.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Debunking+as+Positive+Science%3A+Reflections+in+Honor+of+the+25th+Anniversary+of+Stephen+Jay+Gould%27s+The+Mismeasure+of+Man&amp;rft.atitle=Monthly+Review&amp;rft.aulast=York%2C+Richard&amp;rft.au=York%2C+Richard&amp;rft.au=Clark%2C+Brett&amp;rft.date=February+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.monthlyreview.org%2F0206yorkclark.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Mismeasure_of_Man"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Originally published in <i>The Public Interest</i>: <a href="http://www.cpsimoes.net/artigos/art_davis.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cpsimoes.net/artigos/art_davis.html" rel="nofollow">review</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> (Davis, 1983, p. 45)</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <i>Measuring Intelligence, Facts and Fallacies</i>, (University Press, Cambridge, 2004). p.73</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> ibid. p. 145-46</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Blinkhorn, Steve (1982) <a href="http://www.skepticfiles.org/evolut/mismeasr.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.skepticfiles.org/evolut/mismeasr.htm" rel="nofollow">"What Skulduggery?"</a> <i>NATURE</i>. April 1982.</li>
<li id="cite_note-gottfredson-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-gottfredson_11-0" title="">^</a></b> Gottfredson, Linda (December 13, 1994). <a href="/wiki/Mainstream_Science_on_Intelligence" title="Mainstream Science on Intelligence">Mainstream Science on Intelligence</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Wall_Street_Journal" title="Wall Street Journal" class="mw-redirect">Wall Street Journal</a></i>, p A18.</li>
<li id="cite_note-SenseAndNonsense-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-SenseAndNonsense_12-0" title="">^</a></b> Eysenck, H.J. (1957), <i>Sense and Nonsense in Psychology</i>, p.131.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Revised edition, p.151</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> See "Jensen and Bias: An Exchange" <i>NYRB</i> (October 23, 1980) and <a href="http://www.nybooks.com/articles/7186" class="external text" title="http://www.nybooks.com/articles/7186" rel="nofollow">"What is Intelligence"</a> <i>NYRB</i> (December 18, 1980).</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.debunker.com/texts/jensen.html" class="external text" title="http://www.debunker.com/texts/jensen.html" rel="nofollow">"The Debunking of Scientific Fossils and Straw Persons"</a> <i>Contemporary Education Review</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMiele1995">Miele, Frank (1995). "<a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20041013225203/www.skeptic.com/archives24.html" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20041013225203/www.skeptic.com/archives24.html" rel="nofollow">For Whom the Bell Curve Tolls</a>". <i>Skeptic</i> <b>3</b> (2): 34–41<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20041013225203/www.skeptic.com/archives24.html" class="external free" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20041013225203/www.skeptic.com/archives24.html" rel="nofollow">http://web.archive.org/web/20041013225203/www.skeptic.com/archives24.html</a></span>.  "<i>Skeptic:</i> Let me go back to Gould's four points. Is there any one of those that you think is not a fair and accurate statement of what you said? <i>Murray:</i> All four of them.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=For+Whom+the+Bell+Curve+Tolls&amp;rft.jtitle=Skeptic&amp;rft.aulast=Miele&amp;rft.aufirst=Frank&amp;rft.au=Miele%2C+Frank&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=34%E2%80%9341&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20041013225203%2Fwww.skeptic.com%2Farchives24.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Mismeasure_of_Man"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> Rushton, J. P. (1997) <a href="http://www.ssc.uwo.ca/psychology/faculty/rushtonpdfs/Gould.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ssc.uwo.ca/psychology/faculty/rushtonpdfs/Gould.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Race, Intelligence, And The Brain: The Errors and Omissions Of The 'Revised' Edition of S.J. Gould's <i>The Mismeasure of Man</i>"</a> <i>Personality and Individual Differences</i>. 23: 169-180.</li>
</ol>
